    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - POWER STEERING PUMP: VICKERS (LUK) V10NF AND V20NF - TROUBLESHOOTING - HYDRAULIC
        SYSTEM CHECK
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="2">
        <title>HYDRAULIC SYSTEM CHECK</title>
        <para>After the visual and mechanical/alignment inspections have been performed and it is determined that the
            problem is in the hydraulic system, a systematic and sequential diagnosis must be performed. Evaluation of
            the pump flow rate and pressure will determine if the supply system is functioning properly.
        </para>
        <para>Equipment recommended for these tests includes:</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">A power steering analyzer ZTSE2780 shown in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500514">Figure 14</hotlnk>
                has the ability to measure flow rates from 1 to 10 gallons-per-minute and pressure from 0 to 2350
                pounds-per-square inch. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s05005s_30.xml" xrefid="hl0500505">SPECIAL TOOLS</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0500514" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0500514" filename="../figg05/G0500514.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 14. Power Steering Analyzer</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">A thermometer, ZTSE13281, (Item 2,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500515">Figure 15</hotlnk>) should be used for checking power steering fluid
                temperature.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0500515" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0500515" filename="../figg05/G0500515.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Thermometer</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. STEERING PUMP</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. THERMOMETER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. RESERVOIR</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. STEERING GEAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. FLOW METER</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. PRESSURE GAUGE</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. LOAD VALVE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
